Short Seller Sues Bank of America Corp, JPMorgan Chase & Co, Wells Fargo & Co and Carl Icahn-Reuters
Wednesday, 13 Mar 2013 02:02pm EDT
Reuters reported that A short seller in Herbalife Ltd's stock has sued officials at three U.S. banks as well as activist investor Carl Icahn, saying they are helping perpetuate a fraudulent pyramid scheme at the nutritional products company. Daniel Ravicher, a New York lawyer has filed papers in Manhattan federal court seeking to force officers and directors at Bank of America Corp, JPMorgan Chase & Co and Wells Fargo & Co to pull back $1.2 billion of financing for Herbalife.Â 
